  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, switching channels can be slow. This is somewhat normal since we need to load data, though there is room for improvement.\r\n\r\nHowever, we should still show a loading state when switching instead of just \"freezing\".\r\n\r\nDiscord has something it:\r\n\r\n[Screencast 2023-02-03 11:31:50-discord-loading.webm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11926403/216656354-840dc4ba-b7c1-4783-8eec-6b7e6d2b1a51.webm)\r\n\r\nIt shows \"fake grey lines\" to show it is fetching data.\r\n\r\nI think we have a similar loader already for Wallet? \r\nNeeds design attention.\r\ncc @John-44 @pedro-et ",
