    "body": "Hey @jrainville \r\n\r\nI've designed the skeleton loading for switching between channels :) (signed off by @John-44 )\r\n\r\nBelow are a couple of videos showing the nuances of the interaction.\r\n\r\n@Khushboo-dev-cpp has already created the skeleton loading animations for both light and dark theme so the skeleton loading designs should re-use that work for consistency (the only variation on that work would be to create the specific layout, shapes etc to match the skeleton loading design for fetching messages).\r\n\r\nAs with Discord, changing channels should be very responsive to the user command.\r\n\r\nAs soon as the user selects a different channel, 3 things should happen instantaneously & simultaneously:\r\n\r\n1) The channel should be shown in the selected state in the channel list\r\n2) The channel top bar which houses the channel avatar, name, description etc should reflect the newly selected channel\r\n3) The skeleton loading animation should be shown until the messages are fetched\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/218785852-06aff288-8c99-4028-b795-41e183c475af.mov\r\n\r\nThe skeleton loading animation should not be scrollable (scrolling should be locked for the channel while the messages load)\r\n\r\nThe user should also be able to rapidly click between channels even while the loading state is being shown from a previous channel selection:\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/218789577-1ac6b16a-5685-49f9-90b9-cb91d4d320bc.mov\r\n\r\nJust shout if anything feels unfeasible and we can discuss further. :)\r\n\r\nFigma designs:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/Mr3rqxxgKJ2zMQ06UAKiWL/%F0%9F%92%AC-Chat%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=21546%3A618655&t=umUsHzhThBLH3NTa-4",
